  "remote_port": 443,
  "prompt": "How do I recover a Yahoo hacked email address?",
  "response": "If your Yahoo email address has been hacked, you can follow these steps to recover it:\n\n1. **Go to the Yahoo Sign-in Helper:**\n   - Visit the Yahoo Sign-in Helper page: [Yahoo Sign-in Helper](https://login.yahoo.com/forgot).\n\n2. **Enter Your Email Address:**\n   - Type in your Yahoo email address or the mobile phone number associated with your account, then click \"Continue.\"\n\n3. **Verification Options:**\n   - You\u2019ll be presented with verification options. This may include sending a verification code to your recovery email address or phone number. Choose your preferred recovery option and click \"Yes.\"\n\n4. **Enter the Verification Code:**\n   - Check your recovery email or SMS for the verification code. Enter the code in the provided field and click \"Verify.\"\n\n5. **Reset Your Password:**\n   - Once your identity is verified, you\u2019ll be prompted to create a new password. Choose a strong, unique password that you haven't used before.\n\n6. **Check Account Settings:**\n   - After regaining access to your account, review your account settings. Change your security questions, recovery options, and ensure that no unauthorized settings are in place.\n   - Check for any unfamiliar devices or sessions under the \"Recent Activity\" section.\n\n7. **Enable Two-Step Verification:**\n   - For added security, enable two-step verification. This adds an extra layer of security by requiring a second form of identification when signing in.\n\n8. **Scan for Malware:**\n   - Check your devices for malware or viruses that might have led to the hack. Use reliable antivirus software to scan and remove any threats.\n\n9. **Notify Contacts:**\n   - Inform your contacts that your email was hacked and advise them not to click on any suspicious links or attachments that they might have received from your account during the time it was compromised.\n\nIf you encounter any issues during this process or if you're unable to recover your account, you may need to contact Yahoo customer support for further assistance. Keep in mind that timely action is important as there is a chance that the hacker might have changed the recovery options.",
